<recipe>
<title>
Caramel Apple Oatmeal Cookies
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 15 minutes
COOK TIME: 10 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 25 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: apple, cookie
SERVINGS: 24 cookies
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="0.75">Butter</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0">Sugar</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0">Egg</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0">Flour</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5">Apple Pie</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 350 F. Line baking sheets with silicone baking mats or parchment paper. Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar together until well combined, about 3 minutes.
Scrape down bowl.
Add egg, corn syrup, and vanilla; beat until well-combined, about 1 minute.
Stir in oats, flour, spice, salt, and baking soda until incorporated.
Stir in apple.
Drop by medium cookie scoops (1.5 tablespoons) about 2 inches apart on prepared baking sheets.
Bake for about 10 minutes, or until set.
Let cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes.
Remove to wire cooling rack, and let cool to room temperature.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>